#  Flask App â€“ DevOps Automation Project

A sample **Flask web application** containerized with **Docker** and deployed using modern **DevOps practices**.  
This project demonstrates the complete CI/CD workflow, including building, testing, containerization, and deployment to a cloud platform.

---

#  Overview

This project showcases how to automate deployment of a Flask application using modern DevOps tools:
- Build and containerize the app with **Docker**
- Automate testing and deployment via **GitHub Actions**
- Manage infrastructure using **Terraform**
- Host the app on **AWS EC2**

---

#  Tech Stack

- **Language:** Python (Flask)  
- **Containerization:** Docker  
- **Infrastructure as Code:** Terraform  
- **CI/CD:** GitHub Actions  
- **Cloud Platform:** AWS EC2    

---

# Docker Setup

# Build the Docker image
docker build -t flask-devops-app .

# Run the container
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 flask-devops-app

---

# Terraform Deployment

cd iteraform
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply

---

# Installation

git clone https://github.com/MDFZ-83/flask-app.git
cd flask-app
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py

